  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sri Lanka Drought Well Construction</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	One of the most sustainable ways to provide water is to establish tube wells
&#x2022;	Six tube wells (deep bore wells with a hand pump) will be constructed, to reach at least 180 families
&#x2022;	The hand pump will be an Indian Mark III hand pump which is recommended by the Water Board and UNICEF in Sri Lanka
&#x2022;	Water will be tested for any contaminants (coliforms, heavy metals, arsenic, etc)
&#x2022;	The project will also conduct basic hygiene and sanitation trainings to the communities simultaneously to the hand pump repair trainings
&#x2022;	Tool kits and training will be provided so that communities can repair/maintain the wells</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Over 1,200,000 in Sri Lanka are affected by drought
&#x2022;	A 63% drop in the rice harvest is predicted due to lack of rainfall
&#x2022;	Existing water sources have started to become salinized
&#x2022;	Drinking water has become an issue in 22 or 25 districts in Sri Lanka</narrative>
  </description>
